SIMPLE: growing
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: growing
<hw>growing</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the sequence of events involved in
the development of an organism.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> growth, maturation, development, ontogeny,
ontogenesis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>growing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: growing
<hw>growing</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>increasing in
intensity of some quality.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> increasing(prenominal), incremental.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>increasing in size or amount; <as>as, her
<ex>growing</ex> popularity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>increasing in size and maturity; -- of living things
normally healthy and not fully matured.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flourishing, thriving.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def><pos>p. pr.</pos> of <er>grow</er> (definition 3);
<as>as, <ex>growing</ex> plants</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Growl</ent>⟦br⟧
